The ARIMA model is suitable for extracting the linear components of the original time series, but it loses nonlinear information in the residual [41]. The nonlinear mapping ability of ANNs can reduce the error of the ARIMA model, so artificial neural networks based on the optimal ARIMA model are constructed to improve the prediction accuracy of the model. The specific steps are as follows: First, the optimal ARIMA model was established based on the original series, the fitting value was obtained, and the error was calculated by the following formula:
